article.headline: Yale 43, Princeton 35
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Eric Flato had 12 points to lead Yale to a 43-35 win over Princeton Friday night. Flato was the only player in the game in double figures. Travis Pinick had seven of his 10 rebounds and two pivotal blocked shots in the second half for Yale (8-10, 4-1 Ivy League), which scored the final eight points of the game. Princeton (9-8, 0-3) shot just 26.7 percent from the field and has lost its first three Ivy League games for the first time. The conference was formed in 1956-57. Yale led 35-28 when Casey Hughes dunked off a pass from Caleb Holmes with 6:25 remaining but the Tigers scored the next seven points to tie the game. The run was capped when Marcus Schroeder made a 3-pointer with 2:51 remaining. Pinick made a bank shot with 2:26 remaining to make it 37-35 and then blocked what appeared to be an easy layup by Princeton's Justin Conway with two minutes remaining. Yale sealed the win by making all six of its free throws down the stretch.
